Ismael Yacouba Garba (amụrụ ya n'abalị iri abụọ na asaa n'ọnwa Eprel n'afọ 1993) bụ onye na-eme taekwondo na Niger.

N'afọ 2017, o sonyere na asọmpi ụmụ nwoke na World Taekwondo Championships nke emere na Muju, South Korea. Na 2018 African Taekwondo Championships nke emere na Agadir, Morocco, ọ meriri ọlaọcha na ihe omume 68 kilogram nke ụmụ nwoke.

N'afọ 2019, o sonyere na asọmpi ụmụ nwoke na asọmpi Taekwondo nke ụwa niile nke e mere na Manchester, United Kingdom. N'otu afọ ahụ, ọ nọchitere anya Niger na 2019 African Games nke emere na Rabat, Morocco ma merie ihe nrite ọla edo na ihe omume 68 kilogram nke ụmụ nwoke. Na ngwụcha, ọ meriri Abdelrahman Wael nke Obodo Egypt.
